---
import Page from "../../layouts/Page.astro";

const locale = "en";
---

<Page title="Terms of sale — Engra" description="Engra terms of sale." locale={locale}>
  <section class="py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 prose">
      <h1>Terms of sale</h1>
      <p><em>Last updated: April 2026</em></p>

      <h2>1. Purpose</h2>
      <p>
        These terms govern the sale of Engra software licenses
        by Sylvain Ainama (hereinafter "the Publisher") to users (hereinafter "the Customer").
      </p>

      <h2>2. Product</h2>
      <p>
        Engra is a desktop application for recording and transcribing
        meetings. The license is perpetual and non-transferable.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Pricing</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Starter</strong>: €49 — 1 machine</li>
        <li><strong>Pro</strong>: €99 — 3 machines</li>
        <li><strong>Team</strong>: €199 — 5 machines</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Prices include applicable taxes. VAT applied per current regulations.</p>

      <h2>4. Payment</h2>
      <p>
        Payment is processed through our payment provider.
        The license key is sent by email after payment.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Right of withdrawal</h2>
      <p>
        In accordance with our policy, the Customer has
        <strong>30 days</strong> to request a full refund, no questions asked.
      </p>

      <h2>6. License</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The license is perpetual (no subscription)</li>
        <li>It is tied to a number of machines based on the chosen plan</li>
        <li>The Customer can deactivate a device and activate another</li>
        <li>The license is personal and non-transferable</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Updates</h2>
      <p>
        Minor updates and bug fixes are included. Major updates
        may be offered at a preferential rate.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Liability</h2>
      <p>
        The software is provided "as is". The Publisher shall not be held liable
        for indirect damages related to the use of the software.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Applicable law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by French law. Any dispute shall be brought
        before the competent courts.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Page>
